cs.CL, cs.CV, cs.SD, cs.LG, cs.AI. 

The paper deals with the task of semantic speech retrieval using both visual and textual modalities. This suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories, including natural language processing (cs.CL), computer vision (cs.CV), speech processing (cs.SD), machine learning (cs.LG), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). However, given the focus on learning semantically meaningful speech representations and the use of multitask learning, cs.CL and cs.LG are the most likely sub-categories. The use of images and visual grounding also suggests cs.CV as a likely sub-category.
